WEBVTT

00:02.085 --> 00:04.804
Please, please, please.
Okay, what is this?

00:04.880 --> 00:07.133
We're making sure I'm tall enough
to ride all the rides at Disneyland ...

00:07.216 --> 00:08.684
without having
to spike up my hair.

00:08.759 --> 00:11.308
Buddy,
we are good to go.

00:11.386 --> 00:13.138
- Sweet!
- I have been waiting for this day ...

00:13.222 --> 00:17.022
ever since the doctor pointed to the ultrasound
of your mom's womb and said,

00:17.100 --> 00:18.977
"Either that's a fifth limb"-

00:19.061 --> 00:20.529
Okay, no. Gross.

00:20.604 --> 00:22.982
All right. I want everybody
to eat a lot at home ...

00:23.065 --> 00:25.033
because
The Happiest Place on Earth ...

00:25.108 --> 00:27.486
is also home to the most
expensive churro on earth.

00:27.569 --> 00:31.540
Come on. This is gonna be awesome.
Who doesn't love a day at Disneyland?

00:31.615 --> 00:33.242
Can't you and Mom
go without me?

00:33.325 --> 00:35.623
You're the kid.
I think we need you to get in.

00:35.702 --> 00:37.295
Well, it couldn't come
on a worse day.

00:37.371 --> 00:39.089
The technology sector
is tanking.

00:39.164 --> 00:42.543
We're doing a stock market project
in school, and today's the last day.

00:42.626 --> 00:44.879
We all get a thousand
fake dollars to invest,

00:44.962 --> 00:46.635
and as of
market close yesterday,

00:46.713 --> 00:48.386
I'm in the lead.

00:48.465 --> 00:50.888
I may not be the tallest
or the most athletic,

00:50.968 --> 00:52.891
but someday
I will be the richest.

00:52.970 --> 00:55.143
Which is good,
because the ladies love that.

00:55.222 --> 00:58.146
And I've grown accustomed
to a certain lifestyle.

00:58.225 --> 01:00.478
Do you really want girls
who only want you for your money?

01:00.561 --> 01:02.780
I'd like
to have that option.

01:02.854 --> 01:06.279
Manny, put the stock away
and put your ears on.

01:06.358 --> 01:08.531
Mom, I don't think
you have to wear one of these.

01:08.610 --> 01:10.362
Be a kid! Put them on!

01:10.487 --> 01:13.491
Really? Those shoes? What?

01:13.574 --> 01:16.623
Do you know how much walking
you have to do at Disneyland?

01:16.702 --> 01:19.171
Why do you think they have
so many fat people on scooters?

01:19.246 --> 01:21.340
I like wearing the high heels.
I'm fine.

01:21.415 --> 01:25.045
This is just like that jacket you refuse
to bring when I say, "Take a jacket."

01:25.127 --> 01:27.221
"Don't tell me what to do! I'm fine!"

01:27.296 --> 01:29.549
Huh? And you're not fine.
You're cold and shivering,

01:29.631 --> 01:32.225
and I look like the jerk
who won't give his wife a jacket.

01:32.301 --> 01:34.099
So I do.
And then I'm cold and shivering,

01:34.177 --> 01:35.679
and I brought a jacket.

01:35.762 --> 01:38.390
Are you done with
your boring jacket story?

01:38.473 --> 01:39.975
Because we're going
to hit traffic.

01:40.058 --> 01:43.437
I'll tell you one thing.
I'm not gonna give you my shoes.

01:43.520 --> 01:46.524
Ah! That must be Ethan.

01:46.607 --> 01:48.655
Who's Ethan?
Didn't I tell you?

01:48.734 --> 01:51.157
My friend Bethenny's nephew
is coming with us today.

01:51.236 --> 01:53.113
He moved to town
to go to college.

01:53.196 --> 01:55.949
He's very nice, very smart-
big hockey player.

01:56.074 --> 01:58.748
I know what you're doing.
Really? She was so subtle.

01:58.827 --> 02:02.877
Haley has a thing for bad boys,
which was so me.

02:02.956 --> 02:04.799
Clearly.

02:04.875 --> 02:07.298
So, if she's going to be
leaving the nest soon,

02:07.377 --> 02:09.345
we'd prefer it was not
on the back of a motorcycle.

02:09.463 --> 02:12.137
My college roommate had
a motorcycle. Mmm.

02:12.215 --> 02:14.889
Man, I had some good times
on the back of that thing.

02:16.511 --> 02:18.934
Can't believe you did this.
I'm not gonna babysit Bethenny's nephew.

02:19.056 --> 02:21.479
Alex can have him. Okay, I
don't need your rejects.

02:21.600 --> 02:23.352
Hi, Ethan!
Hi.

02:23.477 --> 02:25.730
I'm so glad you could make it.
Thanks for inviting me.

02:25.854 --> 02:27.856
Sure.
Hi. I'm Al-

02:27.939 --> 02:30.362
My 14-year-old sister.
Ethan, was it?

02:30.442 --> 02:33.036
- Yeah.
- Oh.

