pointing that out to her,

07:03.089 --> 07:06.218
and then I remember
a videocassette flying at my head.

07:06.343 --> 07:09.563
You do not' play the cello. I do.
Even geekier- I'm good.

07:09.679 --> 07:12.353
Okay, answer me this-
I will answer you this.

07:12.432 --> 07:14.685
Why do people
carry cellos around?

07:14.768 --> 07:17.021
You know, people aren't expected
to lug a piano around.

07:17.145 --> 07:18.613
What's the cutoff?
I know, right?

07:18.688 --> 07:21.612
Like, go where the cello is.

07:21.691 --> 07:26.447
Oh, look at this. I think I've inadvertently
set up my 14-year-old with a college boy.

07:26.571 --> 07:28.073
The boy was your doing?
Yes.

07:28.156 --> 07:31.330
Yes, and he was perfect,
and Haley was into him,

07:31.409 --> 07:33.036
until, of course,
we ran into Dylan.

07:33.119 --> 07:35.247
I mean, come on, Dad.
What are the odds of that happening?

07:35.372 --> 07:36.874
It's a small world.
Yes, it is.

07:36.998 --> 07:39.501
See what I did there? It's a ride.
I did. Got it. I got it.

07:39.584 --> 07:42.838
It's just so frustrating because
I know I can't run Haley's life for her,

07:42.921 --> 07:46.016
but if she would let me,
I would be so good at it.

07:46.091 --> 07:49.015
Right, 'cause parents
always know what's best for their kids.

07:49.094 --> 07:51.813
You remember that nice girl at the office
I tried to fix Mitch up with?

07:51.888 --> 07:53.390
No offense, Dad,
but I think ...

07:53.473 --> 07:56.477
I probably have a better sense
of what my kids need than you did.

07:56.601 --> 07:59.195
I think it's cute you think that.
Oh.

07:59.270 --> 08:02.524
Mom!
It was so awesome!

08:02.607 --> 08:06.157
