Certainly seems like him.

13:06.703 --> 13:09.456
Oh, my God. He looked like those
old pictures of Dad from high school.

13:09.539 --> 13:10.961
Mm-hmm.

13:11.040 --> 13:12.508
I'm really into street art
at the moment.

13:12.583 --> 13:14.335
There's a really great exhibit downtown.
I'll take you.

13:14.460 --> 13:18.306
Oh, on what, your Razor scooter?
Mom wants you. Uh- Uh-

13:18.381 --> 13:21.225
Ethan, I've been looking all over for you!

13:24.387 --> 13:27.311
I remember I was on
Pirates of the Caribbean,

13:27.390 --> 13:30.143
and this whole fight with Dede
was really eating at me.

13:30.226 --> 13:33.696
And there was this angry animatronic
wench with a rolling pin ...

13:33.771 --> 13:35.364
chasing some poor
pirate around.

13:35.440 --> 13:38.034
They were on a track,
running in circles,

13:38.109 --> 13:40.328
so he could never
get away from her.

13:40.403 --> 13:42.121
And I remember thinking,

13:42.196 --> 13:44.699
"I can't save you, buddy,

13:44.782 --> 13:46.784
but I'm getting
off this ride."

13:46.868 --> 13:49.291
A-And we-
A-And we were going around a corner,

13:49.370 --> 13:51.839
and I was screaming,
and I swallowed a bug!

13:51.914 --> 13:54.212
Oh, being tall is everything
that I dreamed it would be.

13:54.334 --> 13:56.462
What should we do next?
Sit down.

13:56.586 --> 13:59.806
Where we gonna sit down? The ground.
Here. This is good. Right here.

13:59.922 --> 14:01.424
Oh!
Are you okay, Dad?

14:01.507 --> 14:03.851
No, I'm not okay.

14:03.926 --> 14:06.645
I hate to say this,
but these rides are killing me.

14:06.763 --> 14:09.937
But you're the king of
roller coasters. I know!

14:10.016 --> 14:12.394
Something happens
when you get older.

14:12.477 --> 14:15.196
Guess you can't take it.

14:15.271 --> 14:19.367
One of my favorite things in the world
is doing stupid fun stuff with you,

14:19.442 --> 14:22.742
like pogo-stick basketball or trying
to get a swing to go all the way around.

14:22.820 --> 14:25.323
Next time, we should sit
on a fire extinguisher.

14:25.448 --> 14:28.167
Yes, or a bottle of Coke
and some Mentos. Ah.

14:28.242 --> 14:30.540
Honestly, though,
the way I'm feeling right now,

14:30.620 --> 14:32.588
I don't know if there's
gonna be a next time.

14:32.663 --> 14:36.634
Dad, we can always
find cool stuff to do.

14:36.709 --> 14:39.053
Even if you're old
and in a wheelchair,

14:39.128 --> 14:41.802
I'll take you to the mall and push you
as fast as you wanna go.

14:41.881 --> 14:44.304
Really? You'd do that?

14:44.384 --> 14:46.853
Heck, yeah.
And we'll pop some wheelies too.

14:46.969 --> 14:50.564
That sounds fun. And I'll take you to
the top of a huge hill and just let go.

14:50.640 --> 14:54.645
Okay, we'll nail down the specifics later,
but that- that's really nice.

14:56.187 --> 14:57.939
So, do you still
wanna talk or-

14:58.064 --> 15:00.487
No, go. Ride Space Mountain.

15:00.566 --> 15:02.694
Hey. Hey, uh, at the end,
when they take a picture,

15:02.777 --> 15:04.404
do something hilarious
for both of us.

15:04.487 --> 15:06.114
You're gonna die.

15:06.239 --> 15:09.038
When you see it, not
'cause you're old. Yup.

15:09.117 --> 15:10.915
Whoo!

15:10.993 --> 15:13.246
Lily! Lily, stop!

15:13.329 --> 15:14.501
Dad! Dad, grab her!

15:14.622 --> 15:17.296
Hey! I got ya, you little monkey!
Thank you.

15:17.375 --> 15:20.003
Hey, Cam, I got her.
We're in Fantasyland. Where are you?

15:21.421 --> 15:23.173
Okay, it's Toontown,
not "Toonton."

15:23.256 --> 15:25.054
You've been watching
too much PBS.

15:25.133 --> 15:27.852
Thank you.
All right, honey. Come here.

15:28.761 --> 15:30.604
I don't like this thing.
Yeah?

15:30.680 --> 15:35.561
Well, I don't like running like a crazy person
through Downton- Downtown Disney.

15:35.685 --> 15:38.234
I don't know what to do.
The leash is not the answer.

15:38.312 --> 15:40.064
- You want my help?
- Yes, please!

15:40.148 --> 15:42.071
'Cause I can fix this for you
in about two minutes.

15:42.150 --> 15:44.869
Come on, baby girl.
Come with me. We'll be right back.

15:44.986 --> 15:47.535
Okay. Where we going?
Oh, this way?

15:50.408 --> 15:51.955
Ugh!

15:52.034 --> 15:55.664
Manny, you don't sound very happy
for a kid that is flying an elephant.

15:55.746 --> 15:58.090
I lost to Durkas.
It's not fair.

15:58.166 --> 16:00.794
He wanted to buy IBM
because he thought it was funny to say.

16:00.877 --> 16:04.347
Well, I'm glad that you lost.
Fake money has changed you.

16:04.422 --> 16:07.972
Where is the Manny that used to stop
to smell the roses?

16:08.050 --> 16:10.144
He took a bath on
a solar start-up in San Jose.

16:10.219 --> 16:13.598
You have been so busy burying
your face in your phone ...

16:13.681 --> 16:15.979
that you barely said hello
to your family,

16:16.058 --> 16:18.652
you gave Winnie-the-Pooh
the cold shoulder ...

16:18.728 --> 16:22.073
and you haven't even noticed
that pretty girl in the blue elephant ...

16:22.148 --> 16:23.946
that has been smiling at you.

16:25.610 --> 16:27.954
Not my type.
But still, nice to be noticed.

16:28.029 --> 16:31.329
You see what happens when you're not
burying your head in business?

16:31.407 --> 16:33.535
You're right.
I'll try to be more present.

16:36.579 --> 16:39.332
What the heck's on your feet?
They're slippers.

16:39.415 --> 16:41.884
They're like pillows.

16:43.711 --> 16:44.803
Attagirl.

16:46.005 --> 16:47.632
You're welcome.

16:47.715 --> 16:49.183
Look. Your dad
got her baby high heels,

16:49.258 --> 16:51.010
which we said we were never
gonna let her wear.

16:51.093 --> 16:53.266
- I love 'em.
- You look gorgeous, sweetie.

16:53.346 --> 16:54.939
Oh, my God.
You thought people judged us before?

16:55.056 --> 16:57.309
Wait till they meet Little Miss Anaheim.
Who cares? Look at her.

16:57.391 --> 16:59.018
She can barely move.

16:59.101 --> 17:01.354
Thank you, Dad.

17:01.437 --> 17:04.281
You know what? She's got
pretty good garns for a 3-year-old.

17:06.776 --> 17:08.403
Cheese!

17:08.528 --> 17:11.372
Got it. Thanks, Little John.
Thank you.

17:12.198 --> 17:14.371
Aw.
Oh! They have corn dogs.

17:14.450 --> 17:16.417
We gotta get one before we go back.
They are legendary.

17:16.536 --> 17:18.538
I'll be right back.
Okay.

17:18.621 --> 17:22.046
Haley!
It's me, Dylan.

17:22.124 --> 17:24.798
I'm in the bear suit.
I borrowed it to talk to you.

17:24.877 --> 17:26.753
Why are you
dancing like that?

17:26.837 --> 17:28.760
This is what
Little John does.

17:28.839 --> 17:30.887
Maybe. I don't know what movie
this dude is from.

17:30.967 --> 17:32.685
I'm not even supposed
to be talking to you.

17:32.760 --> 17:34.512
Well,
I'm not talking to you.

17:34.595 --> 17:36.723
No, you can talk.

17:36.806 --> 17:38.729
I know. But I'm mad.

17:38.808 --> 17:40.731
You came back to town
and didn't even call me.

17:40.810 --> 17:42.562
I was embarrassed.

17:42.645 --> 17:46.821
I lost my job at the dude ranch,
and I wanted to get my act together first.

17:46.899 --> 17:48.776
What, the
four-dweebs-on-a-bike act?

17:48.859 --> 17:53.205
Okay, the Dapper Dans are
a Main Street tradition since 1959.

17:53.281 --> 17:54.783
Hey. What's going on?

17:55.783 --> 17:56.875
Nothing.

17:56.951 --> 17:59.249
I still love her,
Ethan.

17:59.370 --> 18:01.668
Okay, how do you know my name?
it's Dylan.

18:01.747 --> 18:04.170
Look, I don't wanna
harsh your day,

18:04.250 --> 18:07.971
but I've never stopped loving Haley,
and I never will!

18:08.045 --> 18:09.672
I-Is this
some sort of joke?

18:09.755 --> 18:12.725
- Do I look like I'm joking?
- Dylan, let's not do this now.

18:12.800 --> 18:15.929
It has to be now.
I've got a parade at 3:00.

18:16.012 --> 18:17.480
Hey, seriously, dude,
back off.

18:17.555 --> 18:20.274
Okay. That was my face.

18:20.349 --> 18:22.693
And you're the one
who needs to back off.

18:24.437 --> 18:26.815
Oh!
Oh. Ho! You-

18:26.897 --> 18:30.447
Okay. This thing's kinda heavy.
I can't get up.

18:30.526 --> 18:33.871
Ethan? Ethan, what is going on?
What are you doing?

18:33.946 --> 18:35.823
Uh, hi, Mrs. Dunphy.
Help me up.

18:35.906 --> 18:38.034
Oh. No.

18:39.869 --> 18:42.543
If I could get up, I would-

18:44.624 --> 18:47.673
Come on, Lily, sweetie.
Keep up, honey. Come on.

18:47.752 --> 18:50.471
Phil, you don't look like
you're doing very well.

18:50.546 --> 18:53.846
Maybe because I officially became an old
man back there at Thunder Mountain.

18:53.924 --> 18:58.054
Oh. Oh, my goodness. You are burning up.
You might have the flu.

18:59.972 --> 19:04.603
A bunch of guys at work had the flu, and we all
drink orange juice out of the same carton.

19:04.727 --> 19:07.071
We should get cups.
Hmm.

19:07.146 --> 19:09.695
Luke, did you hear that?
I have the flu!

19:09.774 --> 19:11.367
Glad we didn't
share that pickle.

19:11.442 --> 19:13.865
Hey, everybody.

19:13.944 --> 19:15.537
Oh, hey- Hey, guys.
Where's Ethan?

19:15.613 --> 19:17.411
Oh, he's staying.
He ran into some friends.

19:17.490 --> 19:20.164
But Dylan got fired, so-
Don't freak out.

19:20.242 --> 19:22.495
We have to give him
a ride home.

19:22.578 --> 19:24.580
And we're back together.
Yay.

19:25.915 --> 19:29.010
Hey, no one goes home
till we hit the Lincoln thing.

19:29.085 --> 19:31.679
Yawn. Don't even
try to fight it.

19:31.754 --> 19:33.222
Yeah, he made us go
when we were kids.

19:33.297 --> 19:37.393
Come on, people. It's a robotic president.
What's not to love?

19:37.468 --> 19:38.970
The robotic president?

19:39.053 --> 19:41.852
So my plan was,
drive Claire and Mitchell home,

19:41.931 --> 19:46.402
put them to bed,
pour myself a big tumbler of scotch ...

19:46.477 --> 19:48.195
and tell Dede it was over.

19:48.270 --> 19:50.523
But on the way out,
we made one last stop.

19:50.606 --> 19:54.486
If destruction be our lot,

19:54.568 --> 19:59.369
we ourselves must be
its author and finisher.

19:59.448 --> 20:02.918
As a nation of free men,

20:02.993 --> 20:05.416
we must live
through all times-

20:05.496 --> 20:09.217
I don't know what happened. Maybe it's what
robot Lincoln said about a man's duty ...

20:09.291 --> 20:12.090
or keeping
the Union together.

20:12.169 --> 20:14.888
Maybe I just chickened out.

20:14.964 --> 20:17.342
But I realized
that staying with my kids ...

20:17.425 --> 20:20.269
was more impo?ant
than leaving my wife.

20:20.344 --> 20:22.893
Now that's not
the right decision for everyone,

20:22.972 --> 20:25.066
but it' was
the right decision for me.

20:25.141 --> 20:27.769
And in that faith,

20:27.852 --> 20:29.946
let us, to the end,

20:30.020 --> 20:32.523
dare to do our duty ...

20:32.606 --> 20:34.108
as we understand it.

20:34.191 --> 20:36.660
So I stuck it out
until they were grown.

20:36.736 --> 20:40.115
Jay, you want
to join me in the Jacuzzi?

20:40.197 --> 20:43.497
And the universe
rewarded me.

20:46.537 --> 20:48.164
Oh, yeah.
Here we go.

20:48.247 --> 20:49.749
Hey, Dad,
roller coaster fist bump.

20:51.167 --> 20:52.384
Whoa!
Whoo!

20:53.586 --> 20:56.214
Whoo!
Whoo!

